data.title: Why does my Philips TV not show a picture and displays "Format Not Supported" on the screen?
data.meta_description:
The TV does not recognize the format or resolution of the connected signal.
This TV only supports a maximum input resolution of 1080i. Other devices such as Blu-Ray players, PS3, and HD-DVD can output higher resolutions, including 1080p or even 4K (2160p).
To ensure that your TV will display a picture:

Set your connecting device to a resolution of 720p or 1080i. Consult the owners manual for your product for the procedure to change the output resolution.
